{
  "guid": "samc",
  "name": "Sample Player (Clocked)",
  "description": "This algorithm plays samples, stretching or shrinking them to fit the tempo provided by a clock input, or MIDI. It is the spiritual successor to the disting mk4 Clocked Audio Playback algorithm, but works somewhat differently. Still, it might be fun to review the video (actually for the disting mk3) here. The algorithm looks at the length of the chosen sample, and uses the current tempo and time signature to figure out a number of bars that best fits. It then adjusts the playback speed so that the sample will fit that number of bars. You can use the Speed tune parameter to adjust the speed – this is particularly useful if the sample is not actually a full number of bars long.",
  "categories": [
    "Sample Player",
    "Clocked",
    "Audio Playback"
  ],
  "short_description": "Plays samples synced to a clock",
